# Trivy ignore file — reviewed, documented exceptions only.
#
# Each entry MUST carry a reason. These are accepted *portfolio* trade-offs.
# TIGHTEN for true production (see ARCHITECTURE.md §11).
#
# How to verify locally:
#   trivy config --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --ignorefile .trivyignore .

# AZU-0012 — Storage Account network rules default to Allow.
# The state Storage Account must be reachable by GitHub-hosted runners (dynamic
# IPs) for `terraform init`/state R/W. A default-Deny ACL would lock CI out;
# tightening requires a Private Endpoint + in-VNet/self-hosted runners — a
# deliberate §11 hardening item, out of scope for the lean baseline. Shared keys
# are already disabled (Entra-only) and TLS 1.2 is enforced.
AVD-AZU-0012

# AZU-0013 — Key Vault network ACL does not default to Deny.
# Applies to the state CMK vault (reached by the Storage Account + CI/operators)
# and the etcd KMS vault (reached by the AKS control plane over its public
# endpoint, per key_vault_network_access = "Public"). Default-Deny would break
# those access paths without Private Endpoints; restricting them is a §11
# hardening item. Both vaults still enforce RBAC + purge protection.
AVD-AZU-0013
